In C++20, referring to the type of a generic lambda parameter explicitly is possible (due to the addition to lambdas of some familiar template syntax):

\begin{lstlisting}[language=C++, basicstyle={\ttfamily\footnotesize}]
auto printTypeInformation = []<typename T>(T object)
{
    std::cout << "     size: " << sizeof(T) << '\n'
              << "alignment: " << alignof(T) << '\n';
};
\end{lstlisting}
